<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900828-0073</DOCNO><DOCID>900828-0073.</DOCID><HL>   Steve's Homemade   Buys Stake in Rival,   American Glace Inc.</HL><DATE>08/28/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C7</SO><CO>   STVEA</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   LINDENHURST, N.Y. -- Steve's Homemade Ice Cream Inc.acquired a majority scoop of American Glace Inc., a closelyheld New York marketer of dessert products that have no fator cholesterol.   Steve's Homemade declined to disclose the exact size ofthe holding it bought or the purchase price.</LP><TEXT>   American Glace's products complement the Steve's Homemadelines of premium ice cream, marketed under the Steve's SuperPremium, Steve's Gourmet Light, and Swensen's brands, andHeidi's frozen yogurt, said Gary P. Stevens, president ofSteve's Homemade. Steve's Homemade also franchisesrestaurants and ice cream shops.   Steve's Homemade recently reported a second-quarter netloss of $86,000, or one cent a share, compared with netincome of $531,000, or four cents a share, in theyear-earlier period. Revenue fell 24% to $6.8 million from$8.9 million. Officials have said, however, that they expectthird-quarter results to turn around.   In over-the-counter trading yesterday, Steve's Homemadeshares were quoted at $1.0625, unchanged.</TEXT></DOC>